			<section class="comment-content comment">
				<p>The network is controlled by the majority of hashing power. So, yes if enough users ran modified clients and mined with fast enough hardware, the rules could be changed. This is a good incentive to current users to keep the network power high.</p>
							</section><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply">
							</div><!-- .reply -->
