			<header class="comment-meta comment-author vcard">
				<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/3a0f58350e09fdca9386d18b5197160c?s=44&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=R' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' /><cite class="fn">Vishwanath </cite><a href="http://blog.brocktice.com/2011/05/22/why-bitcoin-is-smart-and-not-a-scam/comment-page-1/#comment-79443"><time datetime="2013-04-08T04:46:09+00:00">2013-04-08 at 04:46</time></a>			</header><!-- .comment-meta -->

			
			<section class="comment-content comment">
				<p>What prevents someone with coming out with an alternative? I mean i could use the same software as Bitcoin and relaunch a new currency &#8211; &#8216;NewBitcoin&#8217;..what then is the legitimacy of bitcoin as a store of value?<br />
By limiting the supply of Bitcoins the prices have shot through the roof, as people hoard it..does that destroy an economy as it takes out purchasing power that would otherwise have lead to people buying goods and circulating money?</p>
							</section><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply">
							</div><!-- .reply -->
		</article><!-- #comment-## -->
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-brock bypostauthor odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-79797">
		<article id="comment-79797" class="comment">
			<header class="comment-meta comment-author vcard">
				<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/bc9f6a8dfbcf1fd803ef14d05c7ce3c2?s=44&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=R' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' /><cite class="fn"><a href='http://brocktice.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Brock Tice</a> <span> Post author</span></cite><a href="http://blog.brocktice.com/2011/05/22/why-bitcoin-is-smart-and-not-a-scam/comment-page-1/#comment-79797"><time datetime="2013-04-29T12:10:40+00:00">2013-04-29 at 12:10</time></a>			</header><!-- .comment-meta -->

			
			<section class="comment-content comment">
				<p>Regarding alt-coins, they exist and they are gaining some traction. However, there is a strong network effect with Bitcoin. Some of the alt-coins have properties that are more or less valuable to different people. Only time will tell.</p>
<p>Regarding hoarding, everyone has different amounts at which they are uncomfortable holding something as risky as bitcoins. This will lead people to spend/cash-out at different levels and help maintain liquidity. As more people use Bitcoin and more are in circulation, I think most people expect that the volatility will decrease.</p>
							</section><!-- .comment-content -->

